snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Introduction to AnVIL - 2023/03/23
snippet.description:
Stephen Mosher kicked off our *new* AnVIL Demos, sharing an Introduction to AnVIL, describing the context of the research environment AnVIL fits into, ways it support researchers and meets common computational genomics needs, and ways users can get started and find support.

Let us know what you think and share your feedback: https://forms.gle/AK12iVXTjsB7yCUUA.
More about AnVIL Demos and today's Q&A: https://help.anvilproject.org/t/introducing-anvil-demos-starting-march-23-2023/153

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Using the Human Pangenome on AnVIL - 2023/04/27
snippet.description:
Julian Lucas (UCSC) from the Human Pangenome Reference Consortium will describe the work of HPRC and show how to leverage the pangenome reference for your analysis on AnVIL.

Relevant links:
Demo workspace: https://anvil.terra.bio/#workspaces/anvil-workshop/HPRC-Giraffe-Demo-2023 
AnVIL Project homepage: https://anvilproject.org/
AnVIL in 2 minutes playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6aYJ_0zJ4uCABkMngSYjPo_3c-nUUmio
Getting Started on AnVIL Book: https://jhudatascience.org/AnVIL_Book_Getting_Started/

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: WARP Pipelines in AnVIL/Terra - 2023/05/18
snippet.description:
Liz Kiernan and Kaylee Mathews from the Broad Institute described WARP Pipelines, which are workflows written in the Workflow Description Language (WDLs) and optimized for the cloud. They shared where to find them, how to use them in example and your own analyses, and how to learn more about them.

Relevant Links:
- Demo workspace: https://anvil.terra.bio/#workspaces/featured-workspaces-hca/HCA_Optimus_Pipeline 
- AnVIL Project homepage: https://anvilproject.org/
- AnVIL in 2 minutes playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6aYJ_0zJ4uCABkMngSYjPo_3c-nUUmio
- Getting Started on AnVIL Book: https://jhudatascience.org/AnVIL_Book_Getting_Started/
- Q&A notes: https://help.anvilproject.org/t/anvil-demo-warp-pipelines-in-anvil-terra-on-may-18/161/2

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: How to combine data across workspaces - 06/22/2023
snippet.description: Frederick Tan from Carnegie Institution demonstrated the capability to combine datasets in AnVIL and how to leverage workflows to scale your analyses using WDL in AnVIL.

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Interactive Genomic Data Science with Bioconductor - 07/20/2023
snippet.description:
Vincent Carey from Harvard Medical School shared a demo running RStudio and Bioconductor in AnVIL to: 
- Get acquainted with the cloud environment selection process, RStudio's git interface, and precompiled binaries
- Have a look at an app that helps with ontologically aware interrogation of the EBI/NHGRI GWAS catalog
- Explore human pangenome representation and variant calling with the AnVIL package and a copy of the HPRC workspace

Relevant Links:
- AnVIL Project homepage: https://anvilproject.org/
- AnVIL in 2 minutes playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6aYJ_0zJ4uCABkMngSYjPo_3c-nUUmio
- Getting Started on AnVIL Book: https://jhudatascience.org/AnVIL_Book_Getting_Started

snippet.description:

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Epigenetics in AnVIL - 2023/09/21
snippet.description:
In this demo, Ava Hoffman introduced fundamental concepts of epigenetics data analysis and demonstrated how to visualize ChIP-Seq experiment data using RStudio in AnVIL.

Learn more about AnVIL Demos here: https://anvilproject.org/events/anvil2023-september-demos
Give us feedback: https://tinyurl.com/mtxd79wm 
Check out the slides here: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1kSnuHyF36s6FDTLsAPkmnupyp1RcODidNiYYpijjWKg/edit?usp=sharing

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: DUOS - a tour of AnVIL's innovative data sharing platform - 2023/10/26
snippet.description:
In this month's AnVIL Demo, Jonathan Lawson (Broad Institute) discussed the Data Use Oversight System (aka DUOS) which promotes secure data sharing and how it can help with your research.

Visit DUOS: https://duos.org/
Explore AnVIL: https://anvil.terra.bio
Get started on AnVIL: https://jhudatascience.org/AnVIL_Book_Getting_Started/
Sign up for the next AnVIL Demos here: https://help.anvilproject.org/c/demos/5

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Collecting and subsetting SRA data - 2023/12/14
snippet.description:
In this demo, Ava Hoffman from the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center will describe how to pull data from SRA into AnVIL and use a public workflow to subset data into smaller files for analysis testing and training.

Learn about upcoming AnVIL Demos: https://help.anvilproject.org/c/demos/5.
Find the AnVIL Book with the demo instructions to bring SRA data into AnVIL: https://hutchdatascience.org/AnVIL_SRA_Data/.
Find the AnVIL Book with the demo instructions to subset or downsample data in AnVIL: https://hutchdatascience.org/AnVIL_Data_Subsetting/.

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Single Cell with Bioconductor - 2024/05/23
snippet.description:
In this demo, Elizabeth Humphries from the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center showed the Single Cell with Bioconductor activity as part of the AnVIL Demos Book: https://hutchdatascience.org/AnVIL_Demos/single-cell-with-bioconductor-overview.html. 

Learn about upcoming AnVIL Demos: https://help.anvilproject.org/c/demos/5.

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: QC Analysis Pipeline from CCDG on AnVIL - 2024/06/20
snippet.description:
In this demo, Jason Walker from Washington University in Saint Louis presented on the NHGRI consortium Centers for Common Disease Genomics Quality Control (QC) Analysis Pipeline for WGS data available to run in AnVIL.

Learn more about upcoming AnVIL Demos: https://help.anvilproject.org/c/demos/5.
Find the Github Repository for the qc-analysis-pipeline: https://github.com/genome/qc-analysis-pipeline.

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Sharing Data in the AnVIL
snippet.description:
In this demo, Robert Carroll (VUMC) discusses key considerations for setting up a data model when planning for AnVIL data submission.

Learn more here: https://help.anvilproject.org/t/anvil-demo-setting-up-a-data-model-for-anvil-data-submission-on-october-24-2024/230

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Getting Started with your Analysis in AnVIL and Running FastQC with Galaxy in AnVIL
snippet.description: In this demo, Javier Carpinteyro-Ponce and Kate Isaac presented how to get started with your analysis in AnVIL and how to run fastqc with Galaxy in AnVIL.

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Variant Analysis with the VRS Toolkit in AnVIL
snippet.description:
In this demo, Quinn Wai Wong from OHSU and Alex Wagner from Nationwide Children's Hospital covered how to maximize VRS tooling on AnVIL. From launching Terra workflows to running Jupyter analyses, learn more about using VRS in your variant analysis in this recording!

Find the AnVIL Workspace, read the Q&A, and learn about future AnVIL Demos here: https://help.anvilproject.org/t/anvil-demo-variant-analysis-using-the-vrs-toolkit-in-anvil-on-march-19-2025/284/2

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Galaxy Learning and Modeling (GLEAM): Machine Learning accessible and best practices
snippet.description:
Learn to leverage Galaxy-GLEAM, powerful and accessible machine learning tools integrated directly into Galaxy. This presentation covers tabular, image, and multimodal machine learning through a simple user interface to generate high-quality Machine Learning models. We'll demonstrate GLEAM's value with practical biomedical applications, showing you how to tackle common ML tasks effortlessly. Presented by Paulo Lyra from Moffitt Cancer Center.

Ask questions or get help at the AnVIL Support Forum: https://help.anvilproject.org/t/anvil-demo-galaxy-learning-and-modeling-gleam-machine-learning-accessible-and-best-practices-on-september-17-2025/348.
Sign up for future monthly AnVIL Demos: https://bit.ly/anvil-demos.

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: The All of Us and AnVIL Imputation Service
snippet.description:
Learn how to use the All of Us + AnVIL Imputation Service, a tool for increasing the number of variants in population studies. This presentation will discuss the motivation behind creating this new service, scientific validation demonstrating higher imputation accuracy across ancestries, and how to use the new imputation service portal as well as the command-line tool to impute your data.

Find the Q&A from this session at the AnVIL Support Forum: https://help.anvilproject.org/t/anvil-demos-introducing-the-all-of-us-anvil-imputation-service-on-october-15-2025/354
All of Us + AnVIL Imputation Service Website: https://allofus-anvil-imputation.terra.bio/
All of Us + AnVIL Imputation Service Portal: https://services.terra.bio/#pipelines/imputation/run
All of Us + AnVIL Imputation Service Documentation: https://broadscientificservices.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/categories/39900993442459-All-of-Us-AnVIL-Imputation-Service

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: AnVIL meets the new security requirements under the Genomic Data Sharing Policy
snippet.description:
On October 4, 2024, NIH updated its Genomic Data Sharing Policy, mandating that starting January 25, 2025, researchers must store and analyze NIH controlled‑access data on NIST SP 800‑171 (or equivalent) compliant systems. During this demo, the AnVIL security team will provide a brief overview for how AnVIL meets these requirements and answer questions from the community.

Learn more and sign up for future Demos: https://help.anvilproject.org/t/about-the-anvil-demos-category/169

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: AnVIL Data Explorer: Building and Exporting Dataset Cohorts
snippet.description:
Join us for a demo of the AnVIL Data Explorer, a cohort builder for NHGRI-supported genomic datasets hosted on AnVIL. Learn how to register, link your NIH credentials, find and filter datasets, and request access through dbGaP or the Data Use Oversight System (DUOS). We’ll also walk through exporting selected datasets to AnVIL for analysis.

By the end of the session, you’ll understand how to use the AnVIL Data Explorer to find, access, and analyze genomic data in the AnVIL ecosystem.

Learn more and sign up for future Demos: https://help.anvilproject.org/t/about-the-anvil-demos-category/169

snippet.title: AnVIL Demos: Supporting Self-Service Data Ingestion for AnVIL
snippet.description:
Learn about the Submission Workspaces created for AnVIL and how they aim to enable more AnVIL data ingestion processes to be self-service for Data Submitters. This presentation will give an overview of the AnVIL data ingestion process, cover the challenges with self-service data ingestion, and demonstrate how Submission Workspaces help address these challenges.

Slides from the presentation are viewable here: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NhbrcYRTCNUjSYmQ7c2jN-r8U3LzYKBf/view?usp=sharing.

Learn more and sign up for future Demos: https://help.anvilproject.org/t/about-the-anvil-demos-category/169
